led: Semgrep scan failed: Error: Command failed: semgrep scan --config /workspace/patches/observability/ --json /workspace, **When** the fix is applied, **Then** Check Semgrep installation and rules configuration.\nverification/3-2-audit-fix-story-generation-proof.md:116:**Suggested Fix:** Check Semgrep installation and rules configuration\nverification/3-2-audit-fix-story-generation-proof.md:127:**[FAIL]** Cannot verify the zero-gaps path in the current container environment. The required tools (semgrep, coverage tooling) are not installed in the container, making it impossible to create a project with 0 audit gaps. The `[OK] No gaps found -- nothing to fix` message could not be exercised.\nverification/3-2-audit-fix-story-generation-proof.md:139:  {\"key\":\"audit-fix-observability-1\",\"filePath\":\"/workspace/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/audit-fix-observability-1.md\",\"gap\":{\"dimension\":\"observability\",\"description\":\"Static analysis failed: ...\",\"suggestedFix\":\"Check Semgrep installation and rules configuration\"},\"skipped\":true},\nsrc/modules/audit/dimensions.ts:53:        gaps.push(gap('observability', `Static analysis skipped: ${d.skipReason ?? 'Semgrep not installed'}`, 'Install Semgrep: pip install semgrep'));\nsrc/modules/audit/dimensions.ts:65:      gaps.push(gap('observability', `Static analysis failed: ${sr.error}`, 'Check Semgrep installation and rules configuration'));\nsrc/modules/observability/AGENTS.md:8:- `analyzer.ts` — Static analysis runner: `analyze(projectDir, config?)` — runs Semgrep (or skips gracefully if not installed), parses results into tool-agnostic `AnalyzerResult`. Also exports `checkSemgrepInstalled`, `runSemgrep`, `parseSemgrepOutput`, `computeSummary`.\nsrc/modules/review/__tests__/observability-patch.test.ts:41:      'static analysis skipped — install semgrep',\nsrc/modules/observability/analyzer.ts:60:  if (!checkSemgrepInstalled()) {\n\n[Showing results with pagination = limit: 30, offset: 0]"}]},"paren