{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014ML2B6BDhfU7XDuvKmT3MS","type":"tool_result","content":"  1700→| 0-2-ralph-progress-display | Epic 0 | Done (verified) | verify | 0 |\n  1701→| 0-3-run-command-dashboard | Epic 0 | Done (verified) | verify | 0 |\n  1702→| 0-5-1-stream-json-claude-driver | Epic 0.5 | Done (verified) | verify | 0 |\n  1703→| 0-5-2-stream-event-parser | Epic 0.5 | Done (verified) | verify | 0 |\n  1704→| 6-1-rewrite-ink-components-match-ux-spec | Epic 6 | Done (verified) | create-story, dev-story, code-review, verify | 2 |\n  1705→| 6-2-verify-stream-json-pipeline-e2e | Epic 6 | Done (verified) | create-story, dev-story, code-review, verify | 1 |\n  1706→\n  1707→Seven stories were touched this session. Five were carry-overs from previous sessions needing only verification. Two (6-1, 6-2) went through the full lifecycle: story creation, implementation, code review, and verification.\n  1708→\n  1709→Epic 6 (Dashboard Visualization Rework) was completed and closed this session, including an epic retrospective. All remaining work is in Epic 7 (Onboarding — Compliance Gaps), which is in backlog.\n  1710→\n  1711→---\n  1712→\n  1713→## 2. Issues Analysis\n  1714→\n  1715→### Bugs Discovered During Implementation or Verification\n  1716→\n  1717→| Severity | Story | Bug | Resolution |\n  1718→|----------|-------|-----|------------|\n  1719→| HIGH | 6-1 | `updateSprintState()` wiped accumulated `totalCost` every 5s during polling — cost display would flash and disappear | Fixed with field preservation |\n  1720→| HIGH | 6-2 | Test reimplemented production `makeLineHandler` instead of importing — changes to production code wouldn't be caught by tests | Fixed by extracting `createLineProcessor` to `run-helpers.ts` |\n  1721→| HIGH | 6-2 | Story File List had wrong path | Fixed |\n  1722→| MEDIUM | 6-1 | `startsWith` key comparison in `StoryBreakdown` caused false matches (e.g., story `3-2` matching `3-20`) | Fixed to exact comparison |\n  1723→| MEDIUM | 6-2 | `makeLineHandler` was untestable closure in `run.ts` | Extracted to `run-helpers.ts` |\n  1724→| MEDIUM | 6-2 | Unused `vi` import | Removed |\n  1725→| LOW | 6-1 | `run.ts` is 308 lines (8 over NFR9 300-line limit) | Unfixed — pre-existing |\n  1726→| LOW | 6-2 | No test for multi-byte UTF-8 split across chunk boundaries | Unfixed |\n  1727→| LOW | 6-2 | Renderer state accumulation test uses manual switch, not real Ink renderer | Unfixed |\n  1728→\n  1729→**Pattern:** 3 HIGH bugs caught in code review, all fixed before verification. Code review is catching real issues.\n  1730→\n  1731→### Workarounds Applied (Tech Debt Introduced)\n  1732→\n  1733→1. **3-file split for NFR9 compliance (6-1):** `ink-app.tsx`, `ink-components.tsx`, `ink-activity-components.tsx` split to stay under 300-line limit. Adds indirection but avoids circular imports.\n  1734→2. **Cost accumulation data loss (6-1):** `result` event cost only accumulates when `state.sprintInfo` is non-null. Cost from early events before sprint state init is silently lost.\n  1735→3. **Iteration count polling delay (6-1):** `currentIterationCount` is a mutable closure variable updated from stderr. Updates delayed until next 5-second polling interval.\n  1736→4. **Synthetic NDJSON fixtures (6-2):** No real recorded NDJSON logs available. Test fixtures constructed synthetically — may not match real-world stream-json output.\n  1737→5. **`VITEST=1` env var hack (0-5-2):** Container requires this to suppress CLI auto-parse on module import.\n  1738→\n  1739→### Verification Gaps\n  1740→\n  1741→1. **AC5 of story 6-2 escalated to human:** Requires manual `codeharness run` and screenshot capture of real-time Ink rendering. Correctly tagged `integration-required`. Cannot be automated.\n  1742→2. **Static analysis vs runtime (6-1):** Verifier used static analysis of dist bundle rather than runtime rendering. Passes but doesn't test actual render behavior.\n  1743→3. **Observability gaps in pure functions:** `parseStreamLine` (0-5-2) and `codeharness progress` (0-1) have no telemetry. VictoriaLogs returns zero events for all invocations.\n  1744→4. **No integration test for full run->renderer->component pipeline** with cost accumulation across polling cycles (6-1).\n  1745→\n  1746→### Tooling/Infrastructure Problems\n  1747→\n  1748→1. **Stale containers:** Previous sessions left `codeharness-verify` running. Required `docker rm -f` before starting new verification. Hit in sessions 3 and 4.\n  1749→2. **Port conflicts with shared observability stack:** `docker-compose.harness.yml` tries to bind ports already used by shared stack. Workaround: use shared stack directly.\n  1750→3. **`codeharness status --check-docker` false negative:** Reports shared stack as down even when running.\n  1751→4. **Beads sync failure (6-1):** `codeharness sync --story 6-1 --direction files-to-beads` failed with \"Story file not found or has no Status line\".\n  1752→5. **Non-standard sprint status value:** Previous session left `verified` (invalid) in sprint status. Had to normalize to `verifying`.\n  1753→\n  1754→---\n  1755→\n  1756→## 3. What Went Well\n  1757→\n  1758→- **7 stories completed and verified** — strong throughput for a single day session.\n  1759→- **Epic 6 fully delivered** — from story creation through verification and epic retrospective, all within one extended session.\n  1760→- **Code review caught 3 HIGH-severity bugs** before verification — the `totalCost` wipe bug would have been user-visible; the `startsWith` false match would have caused wrong story data to display; the test duplication would have left a silent coverage gap.\n  1761→- **Clean verification on 0-5-1** — all 4 ACs passed without any issues, proving the verification pipeline works well when the code is solid.\n  1762→- **Production refactor improved testability** — extracting `createLineProcessor` to `run-helpers.ts` (story 6-2) made a previously-untestable closure importable and testable.\n  1763→- **Sprint at 88% completion** — only Epic 7 (3 backlog stories) remains.\n  1764→\n  1765→---\n  1766→\n  1767→## 4. What Went Wrong\n  1768→\n  1769→- **Infrastructure friction on every verification run:** Stale containers and port conflicts hit in 3 of 4 sessions. Each time required manual cleanup before verification could proceed. This is pure waste.\n  1770→- **Epic 6 numbering collision:** Two different sprints reused \"Epic 6\" for different epics. The stale `epic-6-retrospective.md` from the old Brownfield Onboarding epic persisted and was misleading.\n  1771→- **NFR9 300-line limit caused unplanned refactoring:** Story 6-1 required a 3-file split not anticipated during story creation. This added complexity without adding value.\n  1772→- **No formal epic definition for Epic 6:** Had to derive intent from story names, UX spec, and existing code. Creates ambiguity during story creation.\n  1773→- **Action item carry-forward rate ~100%:** Retro action items are generated but never executed. The epic-6 retrospective noted this explicitly.\n  1774→- **Proof format brittleness (0-2):** AC3 verification initially failed because evidence reused a bash block from AC2. The verifier is sensitive to proof formatting rather than proof substance.\n  1775→\n  1776→---\n  1777→\n  1778→## 5. Lessons Learned\n  1779→\n  1780→### Patterns to Repeat\n  1781→\n  1782→1. **Code review before verification catches real bugs.** The 3 HIGH-severity bugs caught in code review for stories 6-1 and 6-2 would have wasted verification cycles if missed.\n  1783→2. **Extracting closures to helper modules** when testability is needed. The `run-helpers.ts` pattern from 6-2 is a clean solution.\n  1784→3. **Escalating genuinely non-automatable ACs** rather than faking evidence. AC5 of 6-2 was correctly tagged `integration-required`.\n  1785→\n  1786→### Patterns to Avoid\n  1787→\n  1788→1. **Leaving containers running between sessions.** The verification container should be cleaned up as part of session teardown.\n  1789→2. **Reusing epic numbers across sprints.** Creates stale artifact confusion.\n  1790→3. **Assuming NFRs won't affect story scope.** The 300-line limit NFR should be factored into story sizing during creation, not discovered during implementation.\n  1791→4. **Writing retro action items without an execution mechanism.** If nobody acts on them, they're documentation theater.\n  1792→\n  1793→---\n  1794→\n  1795→## 6. Action Items\n  1796→\n  1797→### Fix Now (Before Next Session)\n  1798→\n  1799→- [ ] **Clean up stale Docker containers** — `docker rm -f codeharness-verify` and any other orphaned containers from this session."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01FVdVXwr4A1SuLMz7rmo6Vd","session_id":"02b06ad8-9233-430d-bd8e-764032ea190c","uuid":"7290c988-e2ae-4bf7-a024-1a3e8a8ab93b","timestamp":"2026-03-21T11:44:28.352Z"}
