{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WvVDNNvsGC5qfY3kGbLPft","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 7.1: Install Semgrep Static Analysis\n     2→\n     3→Status: review\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As an operator onboarding a project with codeharness,\n     8→I want Semgrep installed automatically as part of dependency setup,\n     9→so that `codeharness audit` observability static analysis passes without manual tool installation.\n    10→\n    11→## Goal\n    12→\n    13→Close the compliance gap where `codeharness audit` reports \"static analysis skipped -- install semgrep\" as a warning. Add Semgrep to the dependency registry so it is installed alongside other tools (showboat, beads, agent-browser) during `codeharness init`. Verify end-to-end that the audit observability dimension reports actual scan results instead of a skip warning.\n    14→\n    15→## Context\n    16→\n    17→The observability analyzer module (`src/modules/observability/analyzer.ts`) already handles Semgrep integration:\n    18→- `checkSemgrepInstalled()` checks PATH for `semgrep`\n    19→- `runSemgrep()` spawns `semgrep scan --config <rulesDir> --json <projectDir>`\n    20→- If Semgrep is missing, returns `skipped: true` with `skipReason: \"static analysis skipped -- install semgrep\"`\n    21→\n    22→The audit dimension (`src/modules/audit/dimensions.ts`) propagates this skip as a `warn` gap with suggested fix `\"Install Semgrep: pip install semgrep\"`.\n    23→\n    24→The `DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY` in `src/lib/deps.ts` handles auto-installation of external tools via pip/pipx/npm fallback chains. Semgrep is NOT in this registry — that is the gap.\n    25→\n    26→The verification Dockerfile (`templates/Dockerfile.verify`) already installs Semgrep via `pipx install semgrep`. Semgrep rules exist at `patches/observability/*.yaml`. The code infrastructure is complete; only the host-side auto-install entry is missing.\n    27→\n    28→## Acceptance Criteria\n    29→\n    30→1. **Given** the `DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY` in `src/lib/deps.ts`, **When** a developer reads the registry, **Then** Semgrep is listed with `pipx install semgrep` as the primary install command and `pip install semgrep` as fallback, with `checkCommand: { cmd: 'semgrep', args: ['--version'] }` and `critical: false`. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    31→\n    32→2. **Given** a fresh environment without Semgrep, **When** `installAllDependencies()` runs (via `codeharness init`), **Then** Semgrep is installed (or reports a non-fatal failure if Python is unavailable). <!-- verification: integration-required -->\n    33→\n    34→3. **Given** Semgrep is installed on the host, **When** `codeharness audit` runs against the codeharness project, **Then** the observability dimension reports actual static analysis results (gap count or pass) instead of \"static: skipped\". <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    35→\n    36→4. **Given** Semgrep rules in `patches/observability/`, **When** the analyzer runs against a project with known observability gaps (e.g., catch blocks without logging), **Then** gaps are reported with file, line, rule ID, and description. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    37→\n    38→5. **Given** the existing unit tests in `src/lib/__tests__/deps.test.ts`, **When** the Semgrep registry entry is added, **Then** tests cover the new entry: check-installed, install-success, and install-failure paths — maintaining 100% coverage on changed code. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    39→\n    40→6. **Given** `src/lib/AGENTS.md` documents the deps module, **When** Semgrep is added to the registry, **Then** AGENTS.md is updated to mention Semgrep in the dependency list. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    41→\n    42→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    43→\n    44→- [x] Task 1: Add Semgrep to DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY (AC: #1)\n    45→  - [x] Add entry to `src/lib/deps.ts` `DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY` array after `beads`\n    46→  - [x] Use `pipx` as primary, `pip` as fallback (matches Dockerfile.verify pattern)\n    47→  - [x] Set `critical: false` — Semgrep is optional, audit degrades gracefully\n    48→- [x] Task 2: Update unit tests (AC: #5)\n    49→  - [x] Add test cases in `src/lib/__tests__/deps.test.ts` for Semgrep registry entry\n    50→  - [x] Verify DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY length increased by 1\n    51→  - [x] Test check-installed, install-success, install-failure for Semgrep entry\n    52→- [x] Task 3: Verify audit integration (AC: #3, #4)\n    53→  - [x] Run `npx vitest` to confirm all tests pass\n    54→  - [x] Verify analyzer tests in `src/modules/observability/__tests__/analyzer.test.ts` still pass\n    55→- [x] Task 4: Update AGENTS.md (AC: #6)\n    56→  - [x] Update `src/lib/AGENTS.md` deps.ts entry to include Semgrep\n    57→\n    58→## Dev Notes\n    59→\n    60→### Existing Code to Modify\n    61→\n    62→- **`src/lib/deps.ts`** — Add Semgrep entry to `DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY`. Follow exact pattern of existing entries (showboat, agent-browser, beads).\n    63→- **`src/lib/__tests__/deps.test.ts`** — Add test coverage for new entry.\n    64→- **`src/lib/AGENTS.md`** — Update documentation.\n    65→\n    66→### DO NOT Modify\n    67→\n    68→- `src/modules/observability/analyzer.ts` — Already handles Semgrep correctly. No changes needed.\n    69→- `src/modules/audit/dimensions.ts` — Already reports skip/pass correctly. No changes needed.\n    70→- `templates/Dockerfile.verify` — Already installs Semgrep. No changes needed.\n    71→- `patches/observability/*.yaml` — Rules already exist and work. No changes needed.\n    72→\n    73→### Architecture Compliance\n    74→\n    75→- **Result<T> pattern**: Not applicable — deps.ts uses its own DependencyResult type (pre-existing pattern).\n    76→- **<300 lines**: `deps.ts` is 155 lines, adding ~10 lines for registry entry. Well under limit.\n    77→- **Index exports**: deps.ts exports are already consumed directly, no index.ts wrapper needed (pre-existing pattern).\n    78→- **Test coverage**: 100% target on new/changed code.\n    79→\n    80→### Previous Story Intelligence\n    81→\n    82→This is the first story in Epic 7. Previous epics (1-6) are all done. Key patterns from recent work:\n    83→- Story 6-2 established `run-helpers.ts` extraction pattern for testability.\n    84→- Story 6-1 hit NFR9 300-line limit — not a risk here (deps.ts is small).\n    85→- Code review catches real bugs — ensure the registry entry matches the Dockerfile.verify install approach (pipx, not pip).\n    86→\n    87→### References\n    88→\n    89→- [Source: src/lib/deps.ts] — DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY, installDependency(), installAllDependencies()\n    90→- [Source: src/lib/__tests__/deps.test.ts] — Existing test patterns for registry entries\n    91→- [Source: src/modules/observability/analyzer.ts] — checkSemgrepInstalled(), analyze()\n    92→- [Source: src/modules/audit/dimensions.ts#checkObservability] — Audit dimension that reports Semgrep status\n    93→- [Source: templates/Dockerfile.verify#L18] — `RUN pipx install semgrep && pipx ensurepath` (reference for install approach)\n    94→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-operational-excellence.md#Decision7] — Semgrep integration architecture decision\n    95→\n    96→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n    97→## Verification Requirements\n    98→\n    99→- [ ] Showboat proof document created (`verification/7-1-install-semgrep-static-analysis-proof.md`)\n   100→- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence\n   101→- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n   102→\n   103→## Documentation Requirements\n   104→\n   105→- [ ] `src/lib/AGENTS.md` updated to include Semgrep in deps module description\n   106→\n   107→## Testing Requirements\n   108→\n   109→- [ ] Unit tests written for Semgrep registry entry in deps.test.ts\n   110→- [ ] Existing analyzer tests pass unchanged\n   111→- [ ] Coverage target: 100% on changed files\n   112→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n   113→\n   114→## Dev Agent Record\n   115→\n   116→### Agent Model Used\n   117→Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n   118→\n   119→### Debug Log References\n   120→N/A — single-pass implementation, no retries needed.\n   121→\n   122→### Completion Notes List\n   123→- Added Semgrep entry to DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY with pipx primary, pip fallback, critical: false\n   124→- Added 7 new test cases (registry entry tests + installDependency semgrep-specific tests)\n   125→- Updated 2 existing tests to handle 4th registry entry (semgrep) in failure scenarios\n   126→- All 2920 tests pass across 113 test files\n   127→- AGENTS.md updated to mention Semgrep in deps module description\n   128→\n   129→### File List\n   130→\n   131→- `src/lib/deps.ts`\n   132→- `src/lib/__tests__/deps.test.ts`\n   133→- `src/lib/AGENTS.md`\n   134→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01GwwRGHx2aGkVK7JeqGtRMs","session_id":"02b06ad8-9233-430d-bd8e-764032ea190c","uuid":"c151d57b-f009-4915-b807-e1a2939bd587","timestamp":"2026-03-21T11:50:39.460Z"}
