{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GwwRGHx2aGkVK7JeqGtRMs","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All 38 tests pass.\n\n---\n\n## Review Summary\n\n**Story:** 7-1-install-semgrep-static-analysis\n**Files reviewed:** `src/lib/deps.ts`, `src/lib/__tests__/deps.test.ts`, `src/lib/AGENTS.md`\n**Git vs Story discrepancies:** 0 (all claimed files match git reality)\n\n### Fixes Applied\n\n1. **HIGH — Missing test for `CriticalDependencyError` throw path** (line 149 of deps.ts): Added test that temporarily mutates a registry entry to `critical: true`, verifies the throw. Line coverage: 97.61% -> 100%.\n\n2. **MEDIUM — Semgrep test spec duplicated instead of referencing registry**: Changed `const semgrepSpec: DependencySpec = {...}` to `const semgrepSpec = DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY.find(d => d.name === 'semgrep')!`. Tests now break if someone changes the actual registry entry.\n\n3. **MEDIUM — AGENTS.md deps description omitted `agent-browser`**: Updated to include all four registered tools: \"Showboat, agent-browser, beads, Semgrep\".\n\n4. **MEDIUM — Missing null-version branch coverage**: Added two tests exercising the `version === null` paths in `installAllDependencies` for both `installed` and `already-installed` statuses. Branch coverage: 71.42% -> 89.28%.\n\n### Coverage Results\n\n- `deps.ts`: 100% statements, 100% lines, 100% functions, 89.28% branches\n- Overall project: 97.02% (target: 90%)\n- Per-file floor: all 123 files above 80%\n- 38 tests in deps.test.ts (up from 35)\n\n### Story Status\n\nUpdated from `review` to `verifying`.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- None (no functional bugs in the implementation)\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority):**\n- `skipped` status in `DependencyResult.status` union type is dead code — never produced by any code path. Pre-existing tech debt.\n- Semgrep fallback tests don't assert that the primary command was actually attempted before fallback. Follows existing showboat test pattern, so consistent but weak.\n- Lines 140-141 and 149 have unreachable nullish-coalescing fallback branches (`result.error ?? ''` / `result.error ?? 'Install failed'`) because `installDependency` always sets `error` when returning `failed`. Purely defensive code, cannot be tested without synthetic mocking of `installDependency` itself.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- Branch coverage at 89.28% due to unreachable defensive nullish-coalescing branches. Not practically testable without refactoring `installDependency` to omit `error` on failure (which would be a worse API).\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- None. The change is minimal and follows established patterns exactly.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a3df56ef12f33dc61 (use SendMessage with to: 'a3df56ef12f33dc61' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 48806\ntool_uses: 41\nduration_ms: 266734</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"02b06ad8-9233-430d-bd8e-764032ea190c","uuid":"d408d405-457a-4c53-b337-3dda0352995d","timestamp":"2026-03-21T11:54:59.500Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/7-1-install-semgrep-static-analysis.md — perform adversarial review, fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues found. After fixing, run `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` and ensure all files pass the per-file floor and the overall 90% target. Update the story status to `verifying` when all issues are fixed and coverage passes. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Bugs found and their severity (HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW with brief description)\n- Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority items, tech debt)\n- Coverage gaps (files below floor, untested edge cases, areas needing integration tests)\n- Architecture concerns (patterns that don't fit, coupling issues, missing abstractions)\n- Items sent back for re-development (what failed and why)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`","agentId":"a3df56ef12f33dc61","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All 38 tests pass.\n\n---\n\n## Review Summary\n\n**Story:** 7-1-install-semgrep-static-analysis\n**Files reviewed:** `src/lib/deps.ts`, `src/lib/__tests__/deps.test.ts`, `src/lib/AGENTS.md`\n**Git vs Story discrepancies:** 0 (all claimed files match git reality)\n\n### Fixes Applied\n\n1. **HIGH — Missing test for `CriticalDependencyError` throw path** (line 149 of deps.ts): Added test that temporarily mutates a registry entry to `critical: true`, verifies the throw. Line coverage: 97.61% -> 100%.\n\n2. **MEDIUM — Semgrep test spec duplicated instead of referencing registry**: Changed `const semgrepSpec: DependencySpec = {...}` to `const semgrepSpec = DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY.find(d => d.name === 'semgrep')!`. Tests now break if someone changes the actual registry entry.\n\n3. **MEDIUM — AGENTS.md deps description omitted `agent-browser`**: Updated to include all four registered tools: \"Showboat, agent-browser, beads, Semgrep\".\n\n4. **MEDIUM — Missing null-version branch coverage**: Added two tests exercising the `version === null` paths in `installAllDependencies` for both `installed` and `already-installed` statuses. Branch coverage: 71.42% -> 89.28%.\n\n### Coverage Results\n\n- `deps.ts`: 100% statements, 100% lines, 100% functions, 89.28% branches\n- Overall project: 97.02% (target: 90%)\n- Per-file floor: all 123 files above 80%\n- 38 tests in deps.test.ts (up from 35)\n\n### Story Status\n\nUpdated from `review` to `verifying`.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- None (no functional bugs in the implementation)\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority):**\n- `skipped` status in `DependencyResult.status` union type is dead code — never produced by any code path. Pre-existing tech debt.\n- Semgrep fallback tests don't assert that the primary command was actually attempted before fallback. Follows existing showboat test pattern, so consistent but weak.\n- Lines 140-141 and 149 have unreachable nullish-coalescing fallback branches (`result.error ?? ''` / `result.error ?? 'Install failed'`) because `installDependency` always sets `error` when returning `failed`. Purely defensive code, cannot be tested without synthetic mocking of `installDependency` itself.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- Branch coverage at 89.28% due to unreachable defensive nullish-coalescing branches. Not practically testable without refactoring `installDependency` to omit `error` on failure (which would be a worse API).\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- None. The change is minimal and follows established patterns exactly.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None."}],"totalDurationMs":266734,"totalTokens":48806,"totalToolUseCount":41,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":305,"cache_read_input_tokens":47777,"output_tokens":723,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":305},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
