{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KTtXYBXm8syAZ7xz8SHpAw","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Verification Proof: Story 7.1 — Install Semgrep Static Analysis\n     2→\n     3→**Verified by:** Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) — black-box verifier\n     4→**Date:** 2026-03-21\n     5→**Container:** codeharness-verify\n     6→**CLI Version:** 0.23.1\n     7→**Semgrep Version:** 1.156.0\n     8→\n     9→---\n    10→\n    11→## AC 1: Semgrep listed in DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY with correct configuration\n    12→\n    13→**Criterion:** Semgrep is listed with `pipx install semgrep` as primary, `pip install semgrep` as fallback, `checkCommand: { cmd: 'semgrep', args: ['--version'] }`, and `critical: false`.\n    14→\n    15→```bash\n    16→docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'grep -A 12 \"name: \\\"semgrep\\\"\" /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/index.js'\n    17→```\n    18→\n    19→```output\n    20→name: \"semgrep\",\n    21→    displayName: \"Semgrep\",\n    22→    installCommands: [\n    23→      { cmd: \"pipx\", args: [\"install\", \"semgrep\"] },\n    24→      { cmd: \"pip\", args: [\"install\", \"semgrep\"] }\n    25→    ],\n    26→    checkCommand: { cmd: \"semgrep\", args: [\"--version\"] },\n    27→    critical: false\n    28→  }\n    29→];\n    30→```\n    31→\n    32→Verification of registry count (4 entries, semgrep is 4th):\n    33→\n    34→```bash\n    35→docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'node -e \"const fs=require(\\\"fs\\\");const code=fs.readFileSync(\\\"/usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/index.js\\\",\\\"utf-8\\\");const m=code.match(/var DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY = \\\\[([\\\\s\\\\S]*?)\\\\];/);const e=m[1].match(/name: \\\\\\\"([^\\\\\\\"]+)\\\\\\\"/g);console.log(e);console.log(\\\"Count:\\\",e.length);\"'\n    36→```\n    37→\n    38→```output\n    39→Registry entries: [\n    40→  'name: \"showboat\"',\n    41→  'name: \"agent-browser\"',\n    42→  'name: \"beads\"',\n    43→  'name: \"semgrep\"'\n    44→]\n    45→Count: 4\n    46→```\n    47→\n    48→**Result: PASS** — pipx primary, pip fallback, checkCommand uses `semgrep --version`, critical: false. All fields match spec.\n    49→\n    50→[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction (static file read, no CLI invocation)\n    51→\n    52→---\n    53→\n    54→## AC 2: installAllDependencies installs Semgrep via codeharness init\n    55→\n    56→**Criterion:** When `installAllDependencies()` runs via `codeharness init`, Semgrep is installed (or reports non-fatal failure if Python unavailable).\n    57→\n    58→```bash\n    59→docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'cd /tmp/test-project && codeharness init --json 2>&1'\n    60→```\n    61→\n    62→```output\n    63→{\"status\":\"ok\",\"stack\":\"nodejs\",\"enforcement\":{\"frontend\":true,\"database\":true,\"api\":true},\"documentation\":{\"agents_md\":\"exists\",\"docs_scaffold\":\"exists\",\"readme\":\"exists\"},\"dependencies\":[{\"name\":\"showboat\",\"displayName\":\"Showboat\",\"status\":\"already-installed\",\"version\":\"0.4.0\"},{\"name\":\"agent-browser\",\"displayName\":\"agent-browser\",\"status\":\"failed\",\"version\":null},{\"name\":\"beads\",\"displayName\":\"beads\",\"status\":\"failed\",\"version\":null},{\"name\":\"semgrep\",\"displayName\":\"Semgrep\",\"status\":\"already-installed\",\"version\":\"1.156.0\"}],\"docker\":null}\n    64→```\n    65→\n    66→Key evidence:\n    67→- Semgrep appears in `dependencies` array with `\"status\":\"already-installed\"` and `\"version\":\"1.156.0\"`\n    68→- agent-browser and beads failed (npm/pip not available for those) but init succeeded (`\"status\":\"ok\"`) because they are non-critical\n    69→- Semgrep `critical: false` means its failure would also be non-fatal\n    70→\n    71→**Result: PASS** — Semgrep is processed by installAllDependencies and reports correctly.\n    72→\n    73→[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction\n    74→\n    75→---\n    76→\n    77→## AC 3: codeharness audit reports actual static analysis results instead of \"static: skipped\"\n    78→\n    79→**Criterion:** When Semgrep is installed, `codeharness audit` reports actual scan results (gap count or pass) instead of \"static: skipped\".\n    80→\n    81→```bash\n    82→docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'cd /tmp/test-project && codeharness audit --json 2>&1'\n    83→```\n    84→\n    85→```output\n    86→{\"dimensions\":{\"observability\":{\"name\":\"observability\",\"status\":\"warn\",\"metric\":\"static: 5 gaps, runtime: skipped (validation failed)\",\"gaps\":[{\"dimension\":\"observability\",\"description\":\"/tmp/test-project/src/app.js:1 — undefined\",\"suggestedFix\":\"Add observability instrumentation\"},{\"dimension\":\"observability\",\"description\":\"/tmp/test-project/src/app.js:2 — undefined\",\"suggestedFix\":\"Add observability instrumentation\"},{\"dimension\":\"observability\",\"description\":\"/tmp/test-project/src/app.js:11 — undefined\",\"suggestedFix\":\"Add observability instrumentation\"},{\"dimension\":\"observability\",\"description\":\"/tmp/test-project/src/app.js:12 — undefined\",\"suggestedFix\":\"Add observability instrumentation\"},{\"dimension\":\"observability\",\"description\":\"/tmp/test-project/src/app.js:16 — undefined\",\"suggestedFix\":\"Add observability instrumentation\"}]}},\"overallStatus\":\"fail\",\"gapCount\":10,\"durationMs\":1140}\n    87→```\n    88→\n    89→Key evidence:\n    90→- Metric shows `\"static: 5 gaps\"` — NOT \"static: skipped\"\n    91→- Semgrep ran successfully and found 5 observability gaps in the test file\n    92→- Each gap includes file path and line number\n    93→\n    94→**Note:** Gap descriptions show `undefined` instead of the rule message. This is a minor presentation bug in the audit dimension's gap formatting but does not affect AC compliance — the criterion is \"actual static analysis results (gap count or pass) instead of static: skipped\", which is satisf